( https://anytype.io )

Hey there, it=E2=80=99s time to talk.

We=E2=80=99ve always built Anytype for people to create and connect on thei=
r own terms. It started with Spaces =E2=80=93 a home for your thoughts, not=
es and projects.

With Chats, we=E2=80=99re opening a new chapter: a new way to collaborate w=
hile keeping your data fully in your hands.

Version 0.40

*Chat on Mobile*

Messages, replies, reactions =E2=80=93 the basics are here. But this is Any=
type: you can also add and edit objects right inside your chats. Capture th=
oughts as Tasks or Pages, share what you=E2=80=99re building, and co-create=
 in real time. Everything stays organized in your widgets.

*Notifications* are here to keep you updated when it matters.
*Invites* work without approval =E2=80=93 share a link or QR code and start=
 chatting instantly.

Open Release Notes ( https://releases.any.org/ios-040 )

Version 0.50

*Chat on Desktop*

Your desktop Vault just leveled up.
With a new Chat format, your conversations stay in focus with live previews=
 and updates in one view. Exchange ideas, create, and edit without losing f=
low =E2=80=93 collaboration feels as fluid as writing.

We hope you enjoy using Chats in your daily flow. And if you=E2=80=99d like=
, share with us or the Community the chat use cases you=E2=80=99ve discover=
ed =E2=80=93 within your family, classroom, or team space. We=E2=80=99d lov=
e to hear your stories!

*Chapter 1 is unlocked.*
More updates are already on the way.

Open Release Notes ( https://releases.any.org/desktop-050 )

